{
  "text": "The immersion test was performed on three parallel samples for each alloy. Samples with dimensions of 20 mm wide, 25 mm long, and 3 mm thick were mechanically ground using SiC abrasive papers up to 2000 grit. The ground samples were immersed in a 3.5 wt % NaCl solution at 298 K for 72 h. After immersion, the samples were taken out and cleaned with chromate acid (200 g/L CrO 3 + 10 g/L AgNO 3 ) to remove the corrosion products [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The obtained samples were rinsed with distilled water, cleaned in alcohol, and dried in air. The final specimens were weighed on an analytical balance (ME204E, Mettler Toledo Corp., Greifensee, Switzerland), and the corrosion rate (C R ) for each sample was calculated by Equation (3) [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] :",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "22921930",
